<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>good as a play • good as gold</xh5><p> <i>good as a play—</i>said of smth. very entertaining or intensely amusing: Are they not as <u>good as a play</u>, trying their hand at legislation?</p><p> <i>good as gold—</i>1. <i>(of a child)</i> well behaved; not giving trouble: As soon as a few were bumped off by way of example, all the others became as <u>good as gold</u>. 2. <i>(of a pledge, etc.)</i> faithful; reliable: When one of our representatives makes a commitment, you can rest assured that his promise is as <u>good as gold</u>. 3. quite perfect in quality: The chip, which can be implanted in products, is <u>good as gold</u>. They use it to track the flow of goods from supplier to store shelf. </p> </entry>
